This file tracks the status of releases in the 1.3.x line.

See "Stabilizing and maintaining releases" in trunk/www/hacking.html for
details on how release lines and voting work, what kinds of bugs can
delay a release, etc.

Status of 1.3.0:
================

Candidate changes:

  * r16855
    Don't write empty hashes to props file
    Justification:
    Severely bloats working copy size and causes extra i/o when you have a 
    lot of files, but no properties on them.
    (4k per file on most fs'en)
    Votes:
     +1: dberlin

  * r16350
    Fix issue #1911, where svndumpfilter generated invalid dumpfiles
    when copies occurred and --drop-empty-revs and --renumber-revs
    were in use.
    Justification:
      Invalid dumpfiles are not nice.
    Votes:
      +1: cmpilato, kfogel
      +0: dlr (concept, new to this area of the code)

  * r16806, r16807, r16842
    Convert automatic memory management code into pure Python, so as
    to ensure thread safety.
    Justification:
      Prevents segfaults on Windows with mod_python.
    Thread:
      http://svn.haxx.se/dev/archive-2005-10/0867.shtml
    Votes:
      +1: djames

Approved changes:

   * r16834
     Initialize SVN_ASP_DOT_NET_HACK in the Perl and Ruby bindings.
     Justification:
       Consistent with behavior of the command-line client and Python
       bindings in supporting this work-around.
     Votes:
       +0: djames, dlr
       +1: rooneg
